●
Does the list of hypotheses/tests indicate whether additional hypotheses are taken from 
the original study or modified/added by the team? 
 
 
H* (SCORE focal test): The log of the minimum continuously compounded weekly interest rate 
for the subject to defer payment required by Asians to defer payment falls when Asian ethnic 
identity is made salient. 
 
H1: The results in this replication will be the same as those of the original experiment. That is, 
priming Asian American subjects leads to changes in risk and time preferences.  
 
 
 
 
 
 

 
