Ethnicity salience in priming will be manipulated by assigning either a control or primed 
questionnaire. The method of achieving this effect will be the different questions respondents 
will be asked based on different topics. The majority of these questions are restatements of the 
questions from the original paper modified to fit a survey of the general population rather than 
exclusively to students. Some questions were rephrased and altered, along with additional 
questions being added, to counter possible confounding priming factors in the original study. 
These changes are detailed and addressed in the ​attached experimental materials​. 
 
The manipulation of stakes and whether or not an immediate payment is available attempts to 
mirror the original study exactly. All binary choice games are phrased exactly as in the original 
paper. The "Stakes" dummy variable is determined by if the earlier payment in the patience 
game is $7 or not, as $7 is the higher of the two possible early payments. Additionally, 
respondents either make a choice between an immediate lower payment or a higher payment in 
a week or make a choice between a lower payment in one week or a higher payment in two 
weeks. 
