The choices of each respondent in each game will be recorded. These will be treated as 
indicative of respondent’s rational preferences and used to find the log of the minimum 
continuously compounded weekly interest rate for the subject to choose to the later reward in 
the case of the patience experiment and the minimum risk premium in the risk preference 
experiment using the interval regression method outlined in Stewart (1983).  
 

 
