A variable will be generated that is the product of the dummy variables representing the 
availability of an immediate reward and the stakes of a given choice in the binary game. This is 
in keeping with the original paper, creating "separate regressions for each intertemporal choice 
type." (Benjamin et. al (2010)) Additionally, a generalization of the Tobit estimator will be used to 
find the log of the minimum continuously compounded weekly interest rate for the subject to 
choose to the later reward in the case of the patience experiment and the minimum risk 
premium in the risk preference experiment. 
